      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "@user432843 - not sure if that is (always) the case - OpenJDK compiler <i>eventually</i> generates different bytecode: for <code>object != null</code> : <code>aload</code> <code>ifnull</code> | For <code>null != object</code> : <code>aconst_null</code> <code>aload</code> <code>if_acmpeq</code> - I suspect the first is slightly faster --- depending on code (usage of result, <code>object</code> expression) the exact same bytecode is generated for both"
