      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "@user432843 To my understanding, that isn&#39;t true.  And if it was true, you should be able to show it with a JMH benchmark.  Note that comparing bytecodes won&#39;t show anything ... because the JIT compiler should be able to optimize both versions to native code with identical performance.  And even if it was true, that is <i>rarely</i> a good reason to write non-idiomatic code ... IMO."
